      "text": "Tariff\n\nSkip to main content Skip to footer\n\nLegalRules, Manuals and Agreements Tariff\n\nTariff\n\nWe provide renditions of the MISO Tariff to allow interested parties the opportunity to review Tariff provisions electronically. MISO legal staff makes every effort to ensure the Tariff provisions posted here represent the current language on file with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (\"FERC\"); however, reference should be made to the appropriate FERC filings and orders to establish the filed rates or terms and conditions of service at any particular point in time.\n\nA breakdown of As-Filed Tariff modules, schedules, and attachments is provided below for your reference.\n\nIf you have questions, please contact the MISO Help Center.\n\n#### Tariff - As Filed Version\n\nPosted On - 06-08-2026\n\nThe “As Filed” Tariff reflects language filed with FERC through the date shown.\n\n#### Follow\n\nDownload Tariff - As Filed Version\n\n#### Tariff - Effective Version\n\nPosted On - 06-08-2026\n\nThe Effective Version may contain pending tariff language pending FERC action.\n\n#### Follow\n\nDownload Tariff - Effective Version\n\n- Extranet\n- Modules\n- Schedules\n- Attachments\n- Rate Schedules\n\n#### Modules\n\nHelp With Search\n\nYou can search for tariff documents by title or text within the document.\n\nTo improve your search results, consider these options:Use quotation marks to search a specific phrase.Use AND to search for documents with both \"this phrase\" and \"that phrase.\"Use OR to search for documents with either \"this phrase\" or \"that phrase.\"\n\n### Search By\n\nClear Search\n\nFollow\n\nModule A - Common Tariff Provisions\n\n06/08/2026\n\nFollow\n\nModule B - Transmission Service\n\n06/08/2026\n\nFollow\n\nModule C - Energy and Operating Reserve Markets\n\n06/08/2026\n\nFollow\n\nModule D - Market Monitoring and Mitigation Measures\n\n06/08/2026\n\nFollow\n\nModule E-1 - Resource Adequacy\n\n06/08/2026\n\nFollow\n\nModule E-