tion \n• Include POI bus numbers in application \n• Utilize a standard 2% loss calculation for installed capacity \n• The final COD year of the study used for DPP-2023 projects it 2028. The modeling only goes out to 2028 per engineering (for DPP 2023 projects). \n• Please do not reuse Project Common names \n\nTechnical Requirements (Cont'd)\n\nGoHome\n\n### Application Review\n\nGoHome\n\n…Application Review\n\nGoHome\n\nOverview Deficiency Requirements ofthe Pre Queue Phase\n\n• Upon submittal of an application and deposit, MISO will conduct the application review within 15 business days\n\n• MISO will notify the customer of any deficiencies, triggering a 10 business day corrections period\n\n• All deficiencies must be cured within the first corrections period. No additional time will be provided\n\nApplication Submittal\n\nNo later than April 18, 2024 @5pm ET\n\nMISO Reviews\n\n15 Business Days\n\nCustomer Corrections\n\n10 Business Days\n\nGoHome\n\n### GI Finance\n\nGoHome\n\nOverview Banking Information ofthe Pre Queue Phase\n\nPayment in full is recommended at time of Application Submission. \nAll payments must be submitted in full before a J number is assigned. \n\nMilestone Payment Requirements\n\n• Each payment must be submitted separately; DO NOT COMBINE PAYMENTS \n• D1 – ACH/Wire Payment Only \n• D2 – ACH/Wire Payment Only \n• M2 – ACH/Wire Payment or Irrevocable Letter of Credit \n• Reference the Application ID # in the memo of each ACH/Wire payment \n• Contact gifinance@misoenergy.org for wiring instructions \n• Use the MISO GI – Exhibit II – Letter of Credit Template if choosing this option; it too must include the Application ID # \n• Review the GI – Exhibit II – Letter of Credit FAQ for additional information \n• Upload Letter of Credit to the Application in the applicable area \n• Mail original Letter of Credit to MISO via Overnight/Standard or Certified Mail. The mailing address is listed on the FAQ. \n\nGoHome\n\nOverview Banking Information Continued ofthe Pre Queue Phase\n\nState or Federal Tax Form Requirements\n\n• W-9 Form: An Internal Revenue Service Form W-9 or comparable state issued document for the Interconnection Customer submittin",
